Class NoTargetFoundException

    • java.lang.Throwable

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class NoTargetFoundException
extends AmbiguousTargetException
    Special case of ambiguous target exception when no destination or origin station suggestion is available. It is also thrown to indicate that there is no way to determine a route between two locations. Sometimes this might occur if a route is traveled by not much trams and no connection is available at night.
